{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851156826,"sessionID":"ses_28706504dffefyDEcLGmtXHL4i","part":{"id":"prt_d78fa2d1400177ABxZnyKHib2f","messageID":"msg_d78fa1240001F0Pcx4SZDADic6","sessionID":"ses_28706504dffefyDEcLGmtXHL4i","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d4db621b8c3b41a7a1603156e6870dd0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Error Types & Interfaces (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Define error types in `errors.go`\n20:   - `SessionNotFoundError` with `SessionID` field, code `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`, HTTP 404\n21:   - `SandboxUnreachableError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE`, HTTP 502\n22:   - `SandboxTimeoutError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT`, HTTP 504\n23:   - `JWTSigningError` with `Err` field, code `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED`, HTTP 500\n24:   - `ServerOverloadedError` with code `SERVER_OVERLOADED`, HTTP 429\n25:   - `NoEntryPointError` with code `NO_ENTRY_POINT`, HTTP 404\n26:   - All errors implement `APIStatus` interface: `Status() int`, `Code() string`, `Message() string`\n27:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n28:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestErrorTypes -v`\n29: \n30: - [ ] **T1.2**: Define `APIStatus` interface\n31:   - Methods: `Status() int`, `Code() string`, `Message() string`\n32:   - All error types implement this interface\n33:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n34:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestAPIStatus -v`\n35: \n36: ### Phase 2: Config & Constants (ST-2)\n37: \n38: - [ ] **T2.1**: Define `Config` struct in `config.go`\n39:   - `Port int` (default 8080)\n40:   - `EnableTLS bool`\n41:   - `TLSCert string`\n42:   - `TLSKey string`\n43:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` (default 1000)\n44:   - `Debug bool`\n45:   - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n46:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig -v`\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `DefaultConfig()` function\n49:   - Returns `Config{Port: 8080, EnableTLS: false, MaxConcurrentRequests: 1000}`\n50:   - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n51:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultConfig -v`\n52: \n53: - [ ] **T2.3**: Define constants in `jwt.go`\n54:   - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n55:   - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n56:   - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n57:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n58:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConstants -v`\n59: \n60: ### Phase 3: Store Interface & Logger (ST-3)\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T3.1**: Define `Store` interface for router\n63:   - `GetSession(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n64:   - `CreateSession(ctx, sandboxInfo) error`\n65:   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID) error`\n66:   - File: `pkg/router/store.go` (or import from pkg/store)\n67:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestStoreInterface -v`\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T3.2**: Define `Logger` interface\n70:   - Methods: `Info(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Error(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Warning(msg, keysAndValues...)`\n71:   - File: `pkg/router/logger.go`\n72:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggerInterface -v`\n73: \n74: ### Phase 4: JWTManager (ST-4)\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T4.1**: Define `JWTManager` interface\n77:   - `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace) (string, error)`\n78:   - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx) error`\n79:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n80:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerInterface -v`\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T4.2**: Define `jwtManager` struct\n83:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n84:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n85:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface`\n86:   - `namespace string`\n87:   - `logger Logger`\n88:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n89:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerStruct -v`\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement RSA key generation\n92:   - `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n93:   - Private key: PKCS1 PEM encoding\n94:   - Public key: PKIX PEM encoding\n95:   - Helper functions: `encodePrivateKeyPEM`, `encodePublicKeyPEM`, `loadPrivateKeyPEM`\n96:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n97:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestRSAKeyGeneration -v`\n98: \n99: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `NewJWTManager(kubeClient, namespace, logger)` constructor\n100:   - Generate RSA 2048-bit key pair\n101:   - Initialize struct with all fields\n102:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n103:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)` method\n106:   - Create JWT with claims: `exp` (now+5m), `iat` (now), `iss=\"agentcube-router\"`\n107:   - Add custom claims: `kind`, `name`, `namespace`\n108:   - Sign with RS256 algorithm\n109:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n110:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager_GenerateToken -v`\n111: \n112: - [ ] **T4.6**: Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` method\n113:   - Create K8s Secret with name `picod-router-identity`\n114:   - Handle `AlreadyExists` by loading existing secret\n115:   - Load keys from secret data\n116:   - Use `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default \"default\")\n117:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n118:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret -v`\n119: \n120: ### Phase 5: SessionManager (ST-5)\n121: \n122: - [ ] **T5.1**: Define `SessionManager` interface\n123:   - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n124:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n125:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManagerInterface -v`\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T5.2**: Define `manager` struct\n128:   - `storeClient Store`\n129:   - `workloadMgrAddr string`\n130:   - `httpClient *http.Client`\n131:   - `logger Logger`\n132:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n133:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestManagerStruct -v`\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `NewSessionManager(store, logger)` constructor\n136:   - Read `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var (required, fail if missing)\n137:   - Configure HTTP client: `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n138:   - Configure HTTP2: `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n139:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n140:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewSessionManager -v`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` method\n143:   - If `sessionID` empty: call `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n144:   - If `sessionID` present: call `storeClient.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)`\n145:   - Return `SandboxInfo` or error\n146:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n147:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession -v`\n148: \n149: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` internal method\n150:   - Build `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace\n151:   - POST to `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n152:   - POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n153:   - Add K8s SA token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` if available\n154:   - Parse `CreateSandboxResponse` and store via `CreateSession`\n155:   - Use namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default \"default\")\n156:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n157