{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851341308,"sessionID":"ses_28706504dffefyDEcLGmtXHL4i","part":{"id":"prt_d78fd057e001fO2X6lz9eEGvmj","messageID":"msg_d78fabf2e001nLMx1hn0m80Gp5","sessionID":"ses_28706504dffefyDEcLGmtXHL4i","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-5af3c487849d4d8488abcf735d7a8622","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md","content":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-010 — Router 会话管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Error Types & Interfaces (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Define error types in `errors.go`\n  - `SessionNotFoundError` with `SessionID` field, code `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`, HTTP 404\n  - `SandboxUnreachableError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE`, HTTP 502\n  - `SandboxTimeoutError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT`, HTTP 504\n  - `JWTSigningError` with `Err` field, code `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED`, HTTP 500\n  - `ServerOverloadedError` with code `SERVER_OVERLOADED`, HTTP 429\n  - `NoEntryPointError` with code `NO_ENTRY_POINT`, HTTP 404\n  - `WorkloadManagerError` with dynamic status code\n  - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionNotFoundError -v`\n\n- [x] **T1.2**: Define `APIStatus` interface\n  - Methods: `Status() int`, `Code() string`, `Message() string`\n  - All error types implement this interface\n  - File: `pkg/router/doc.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestAPIStatusInterface -v`\n\n### Phase 2: Config & Constants (ST-2)\n\n- [x] **T2.1**: Define `Config` struct in `config.go`\n  - `Port string` (default \":8080\")\n  - `EnableTLS bool`\n  - `TLSCert string`\n  - `TLSKey string`\n  - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` (default 1000)\n  - `Debug bool`\n  - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.2**: Implement `DefaultConfig()` function\n  - Returns `Config{Port: \":8080\", EnableTLS: false, MaxConcurrentRequests: 1000}`\n  - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewServerNilConfig -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.3**: Define constants in `jwt.go`\n  - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n  - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n  - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n  - `PrivateKeyDataKey = \"private.pem\"`\n  - `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"`\n  - `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` (overridden by AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env)\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerTokenExpiration -v`\n\n### Phase 3: Interfaces (ST-3)\n\n- [x] **T3.1**: Define `Store` interface in `doc.go`\n  - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n  - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error`\n  - File: `pkg/router/doc.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [x] **T3.2**: Define `Logger` interface in `doc.go`\n  - Methods: `Info(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Error(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Warning(msg, keysAndValues...)`\n  - File: `pkg/router/doc.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggingMiddleware -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.3**: Define `SessionManager` interface in `doc.go`\n  - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - File: `pkg/router/doc.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager -v`\n\n- [x] **T3.4**: Define `JWTManagerInterface` interface in `doc.go`\n  - `GenerateToken(claims) (string, error)`\n  - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx) error`\n  - File: `pkg/router/doc.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager -v`\n\n### Phase 4: JWTManager Implementation (ST-4)\n\n- [x] **T4.1**: Implement `JWTManager` struct\n  - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n  - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n\n- [x] **T4.2**: Implement RSA key generation\n  - `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)` in `NewJWTManager()`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v`\n\n- [x] **T4.3**: Implement PEM encoding helpers\n  - `encodePrivateKeyPEM(key)` - PKCS1 PEM encoding\n  - `encodePublicKeyPEM(key)` - PKIX PEM encoding\n  - `loadPrivateKeyPEM(data)` - Parse PKCS1 PEM\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM -v`\n\n- [x] **T4.4**: Implement `GenerateToken(claims)` method\n  - Create JWT with claims: `exp` (now+5m), `iat` (now), `iss=\"agentcube-router\"`\n  - Merge custom claims into token\n  - Sign with RS256 algorithm\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGenerateToken -v`\n\n- [x] **T4.5**: Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` method\n  - Placeholder for in-cluster secret persistence\n  - Returns warning when not in cluster\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [x] **T4.6**: Implement `GetPublicKey()` method\n  - Returns `*rsa.PublicKey` for token verification\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v`\n\n### Phase 5: SessionManager Implementation (ST-5)\n\n- [x] **T5.1**: Implement `sessionManager` struct\n  - `storeClient Store`\n  - `workloadMgrAddr string`\n  - `httpClient *http.Client`\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [x] **T5.2**: Implement `NewSessionManager(store)` constructor\n  - Read `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var (required, fail if missing)\n  - Configure HTTP client: `Timeout=2m`, HTTP2 enabled\n  - `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewSessionManagerRequiresWorkloadManagerURL -v`\n\n- [x] **T5.3**: Implement `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` method\n  - If `sessionID` empty: call `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n  - If `sessionID` present: call `storeClient.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)`\n  - Return `SandboxInfo` or `SessionNotFoundError`\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManagerGetSandboxBySessionWithExistingSession -v`\n\n- [x] **T5.4**: Implement `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` internal method\n  - Build `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace\n  - POST to `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n  - POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n  - Add K8s SA token via `readServiceAccountToken()` if available\n  - Parse `CreateSandboxResponse` and store via `StoreSandbox`\n  - Set `ExpiresAt` to `CreatedAt + 30min`\n  - Return error for unsupported kind\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManagerCreateSandbox -v`\n\n- [x] **T5.5**: Implement `readServiceAccountToken()` helper\n  - Read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n  - Return trimmed token string\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReadServiceAccountToken -v`\n\n### Phase 6: Middleware Implementation (ST-6)\n\n- [x] **T6.1**: Implement `concurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent)` function\n  - Use buffered channel as semaphore\n  - Capacity = `maxConcurrent` (default 1000 if <=0)\n  - `sem <- struct{}{}` to acquire slot (deferred release)\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddlewareUnderLimit -v`\n\n- [x] **T6.2**: Implement 429 overload response\n  - `select` with `default` case when semaphore full\n  - Return HTTP 429 with `{\"error\": \"server overloaded\", \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}`\n  - Call `c.Abort()` to stop processing\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddlewareOverLimit -v`\n\n- [x] **T6.3**: Implement `loggingMiddleware(logger)` function\n  - Log request method, path, status, duration\n  - Use `logger.Info(\"request\", ...)` with keys\n  - Handle nil logger gracefully\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggingMiddleware -v`\n\n- [x] **T6.4**: Implement `recoveryMiddleware(logger)` function\n  - Recover from panics with `defer`\n  - Log error with path, method\n  - Return HTTP 500 with `{\"error\": \"internal server error\"}`\n  - Call `c.Abort()`\n  - Handle nil logger gracefully\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestRecoveryMiddleware -v`\n\n### Phase 7: Reverse Proxy Implementation (ST-7)\n\n- [x] **T7.1**: Implement `ReverseProxyWrapper` struct\n  - `director func(*http.Request)`\n  - `modifyResponse func(*http.Response) error`\n  - `errorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, *http.Request, error)`\n  - Methods: `Director()`, `ModifyResponse()`, `ErrorHandler()`\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [x] **T7.2**: Implement `newReverseProxy(target, jwt, sessionID)` function\n  - Create `ReverseProxyWrapper` with configured functions\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n\n- [x] **T7.3**: Implement `Director` function\n  - Path normalization: add leading `/` if missing\n  - Set `req.URL.Scheme`, `req.URL.Host`, `req.URL.Path`\n  - Set `req.Host` to target host\n  - Set forwarding headers: `X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For`\n  - Inject JWT: `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` if jwt non-empty\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestBuildTargetURL -v`\n\n- [x] **T7.4**: Implement `ModifyResponse` function\n  - Add `x-agentcube-session-id` header to response\n  - Value is the resolved session ID\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n\n- [x] **T7.5**: Implement `ErrorHandler` function\n  - Check for \"connection refused\" → HTTP 502 `sandbox unreachable`\n  - Check for \"timeout\" → HTTP 504 `sandbox timeout`\n  - Other errors → HTTP 502\n  - Return JSON response: `{\"error\": \"<message>\"}`\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n\n- [x] **T7.6**: Implement `selectEntryPoint(entryPoints, invocationPath)` helper\n  - Find matching entry point by path prefix (HasPrefix)\n  - Default to first entry point if no match\n  - Return nil if `entryPoints` is empty\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSelectEntryPoint -v`\n\n- [x] **T7.7**: Implement `buildTargetURL(entryPoint)` helper\n  - Parse `entryPoint.Endpoint` as URL\n  - Add protocol prefix if missing: `entryPoint.Protocol + \"://\" + endpoint`\n  - Return parsed `url.URL`\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestBuildTargetURL -v`\n\n### Phase 8: Server & Handlers Implementation (ST-8)\n\n- [x] **T8.1**: Implement `Server` struct\n  - `config *Config`\n  - `engine *gin.Engine`\n  - `httpServer *http.Server`\n  - `sessionManager SessionManager`\n  - `storeClient Store`\n  - `httpTransport *http.Transport`\n  - `jwtManager *JWTManager`\n  - `logger Logger`\n  - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewServer -v`\n\n- [x] **T8.2**: Implement `NewServer(config, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, logger)` constructor\n  - Create `engine := gin.New()`\n  - Set Gin mode: `gin.ReleaseMode` if `!config.Debug`\n  - Initialize `httpTransport`